  "prompt": "What's the difference between tortilla chips and nachos?",
  "response": "The main difference between tortilla chips and nachos lies in their composition and presentation.\n\n**Tortilla Chips:**\n- Tortilla chips are typically made from corn tortillas that are cut into triangles and then fried or baked until crispy.\n- They are generally served plain and are often used as a snack or accompaniment to dips such as salsa, guacamole, or queso.\n\n**Nachos:**\n- Nachos start with tortilla chips but are topped with various ingredients, making them a dish rather than just a snack.\n- Common toppings for nachos include melted cheese, jalape\u00f1os, sour cream, guacamole, beans, meat (like shredded chicken or ground beef), and other toppings.\n- Nachos are typically served as a shareable appetizer or main dish.\n\nIn summary, tortilla chips are the base item, while nachos are a prepared dish that includes tortilla chips along with toppings.",
